    Note:
    Runa Advanced Standard Library: GC Visualization Module

    Provides visualization tools for garbage collector state, cycles, and performance.

    Features:
    - Real-time visualization of GC state and cycles
    - Performance and pause time visualization
    - Integration with developer dashboards and IDEs
    - Extensible hooks for custom visualizations
    - AI/agent-friendly visualization APIs
    - Production-ready, robust, and extensible
    :End Note

    Note: GC Visualization Types and Interfaces
    Type called "GCVisualizer":
        visualize_state as Function that takes gc as GCAlgorithm returns VisualizationData
        visualize_cycles as Function that takes gc as GCAlgorithm returns VisualizationData
        export_dashboard as Function that takes data as VisualizationData returns None
        metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

    Type called "VisualizationData":
        data as Any
        format as String
        metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

    Note: Core GC Visualization Functions
    Process called "visualize_state" that takes visualizer as GCVisualizer and gc as GCAlgorithm returns VisualizationData:
        Note: Visualizes GC state
        Return VisualizationData

    Process called "visualize_cycles" that takes visualizer as GCVisualizer and gc as GCAlgorithm returns VisualizationData:
        Note: Visualizes GC cycles
        Return VisualizationData

    Process called "export_dashboard" that takes visualizer as GCVisualizer and data as VisualizationData returns None:
        Note: Exports visualization to dashboard
        Return None 

    Note: Live Interactive Visualization
    Process called "start_live_dashboard" that takes visualizer as GCVisualizer and gc as GCAlgorithm returns None:
        Note: Starts a live dashboard for GC visualization
        While dashboard is active:
            Let data be visualizer.visualize_state(gc)
            update_dashboard(data)
            wait for update_interval
        Return None

    Process called "register_event_hook" that takes visualizer as GCVisualizer and event as String and handler as Function returns None:
        Note: Registers a handler for GC events (collection, pause, error)
        visualizer.event_hooks[event] = handler
        Return None

    Process called "integrate_with_ide" that takes visualizer as GCVisualizer and ide as DeveloperIDE returns None:
        Note: Integrates GC visualization with developer IDE
        ide.register_visualization_tool(visualizer)
        Return None 